					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2240386#post-2801161</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2240386/scp-2761#post-2801161</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 25 Apr 2017 15:13:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>OZ Ouroboros</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1743859</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Heheh, an actual Bananazilla pic.</p> <p>I imagine the frill kinda working this monster from Ultraman called <a href="http://jbwid.com/img_07/092607c.jpg">Gabora</a>. And he still has a tail <em>(Actually still very long, for balance, cause he's a near 40 foot gator-fish-banana thing)</em> that, like you said, kinda looks like a giant banana stem, maybe with a fin on it.</p> <p>It terms of body proportions, it's surprisingly symmetrical. Probably a few banana &quot;brown spots&quot;, which are the closest it gets to what you might call &quot;tumors&quot; but he's nowhere Cronenberg disfigurement or anything, haha.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2240386#post-2801144</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2240386/scp-2761#post-2801144</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 25 Apr 2017 14:57:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Bassoe</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3070028</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm kind of curious how the structure of his frill works. If I'm picturing it correctly, something like a mixture of <a href="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/CuitWVJWYAAxycK.jpg">this picture</a> and <a href="http://pacificrim.wikia.com/wiki/Raiju/Gallery">the unfolding head/inner jaw of Raiju from Pacific Rim</a>.</p> <p>Also, what's his tail consist of? I'd been imagining one of the following:</p> <p>• None. He used to have one, but after eating a D-Class and becoming bipedal, he shed it and now has human buttocks.</p> <p>• Small in comparison to the rest of his body, brown and remarkably resembling a banana stem.</p> <p>• A pipefish tail but scaled proportionally to the rest of his body.</p> <p>Finally, are the various anatomical structures <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CannibalismSuperpower">borrowed from his prey</a> arranged symmetrically or not? I can equally well picture him either way, as a massive mutated patchwork like shin godzilla but yellow and banana-smelling, or with all the various parts of his body fitting together as naturally as if they were supposed to be that way.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
